    "description": {
      "value": "\r\n<p class=\"source\"><b>Source</b> <a title=\"PZO1115\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1601252463/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=1601252463&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwd20pfs-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">PZO1115</a></p>\r\n<p>A bone, leather, or wooden scroll case easily holds four <a class=\"spell\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/scrolls\">scrolls</a>; you can cram more inside but retrieving any of them becomes a <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Full-Round-Actions\">full-round action</a> rather than a <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Move-Actions\">move action</a>. You must destroy the scroll case to damage its contents (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/equipment/damaging-objects#TOC-Hardness\">hardness</a> 2 for leather or 5 for wood, 2 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Hit-Points\">hit points</a>, Break DC 15). A scroll case is not water-tight.</p>\r\n"
